765
01:03:57.830 --> 01:03:58.870
We have approved

766
01:03:59.030 --> 01:04:02.270
many popular participation mechanisms.

767
01:04:03.910 --> 01:04:05.270
Generally speaking,

768
01:04:05.710 --> 01:04:09.190
us members of the Convention,
that is where we come from.


769
01:04:09.630 --> 01:04:11.710
We are part of these people.

770
01:04:12.470 --> 01:04:16.150
It's not just a number, it's the reality.

771
01:04:16.310 --> 01:04:19.710
When we discuss the various issues

772
01:04:19.870 --> 01:04:23.750
of the new Constitution,
regulatory or more important ones,


773
01:04:23.910 --> 01:04:26.190
we see that we all have shared history.

774
01:04:26.350 --> 01:04:28.670
Nobody told us about public health,

775
01:04:28.830 --> 01:04:32.910
nobody told us stories
about public education,


776
01:04:33.070 --> 01:04:35.470
we experienced it firsthand.

777
01:04:36.070 --> 01:04:38.190
And that is very precious.

778
01:04:38.870 --> 01:04:41.990
It's a process of constant debate.

779
01:04:42.270 --> 01:04:45.230
We are also constantly listening

780
01:04:45.390 --> 01:04:49.190
to the citizens, the young people,
the children.


781
01:04:49.510 --> 01:04:53.990
I think it's quite an intense process.

782
01:04:54.710 --> 01:04:57.030
The most intense process
I've been involved with.


783
01:04:57.190 --> 01:04:58.350
In your life?

784
01:04:59.070 --> 01:05:03.070
It's like playing in a chess tournament,
but every day.


785
01:05:03.470 --> 01:05:05.030
It's very, very intense.

786
01:05:12.310 --> 01:05:15.910
When we began this process,

787
01:05:16.390 --> 01:05:20.670
we didn't only think about
the constitutional text.


788
01:05:21.110 --> 01:05:22.630
We did it, thinking that

789
01:05:22.790 --> 01:05:25.790
writing a new Constitution,

790
01:05:25.950 --> 01:05:29.710
the first one written
in a democratic context,


791
01:05:29.870 --> 01:05:33.150
the first one in the world
to be written with equality,


792
01:05:33.510 --> 01:05:35.910
was one stage of a journey.

793
01:05:37.870 --> 01:05:41.550
For decades,
we've been fighting for matters


794
01:05:41.750 --> 01:05:42.870
that are partial:

795
01:05:43.030 --> 01:05:46.630
we fight for free, decent,
non-sexist public education,


796
01:05:46.790 --> 01:05:51.750
we fight against
specific extractive projects.


797
01:05:51.910 --> 01:05:54.390
Gradually,
we are generalizing our outlook.


798
01:05:54.550 --> 01:05:56.950
We fight against patriarchal violence,

799
01:05:57.110 --> 01:06:00.230
probably one of the most general issues.

800
01:06:01.270 --> 01:06:05.390
But now, we'll be addressing everything
at the same time.


801
01:06:06.190 --> 01:06:07.430
Everything.

802
01:06:07.630 --> 01:06:10.630
That will probably cause an earthquake.

803
01:06:12.550 --> 01:06:14.350
My name is Valentina Miranda.

804
01:06:14.510 --> 01:06:15.670
I live in Lo Espejo,

805
01:06:15.830 --> 01:06:18.270
one of the poorest municipalities
in Chile.


806
01:06:18.430 --> 01:06:20.390
I am a radical and homosexual activist,

807
01:06:20.550 --> 01:06:22.150
a young, feminist woman,

808
01:06:22.310 --> 01:06:25.670
ex-representative of the
Federation of High-school Associations,


809
01:06:25.830 --> 01:06:27.790
the first in my family
to go to university,


810
01:06:27.950 --> 01:06:31.550
born of public education
and a humble family,


811
01:06:31.750 --> 01:06:33.110
daughter of the slums.

812
01:06:33.270 --> 01:06:37.150
I grew up surrounded by drugs,
poverty and extractivism,


813
01:06:37.310 --> 01:06:39.470
violation of human rights and corruption.

814
01:06:39.670 --> 01:06:43.950
I am 21 years old, a hick,
a bumpkin, scum, an Indian.


815
01:06:44.110 --> 01:06:46.990
Proud to be a campaigner
for the Communist Youth.


816
01:06:47.150 --> 01:06:51.270
I am convinced that the Constitution
written here will be ecological,


817
01:06:51.430 --> 01:06:54.830
feminist, multinational, intercultural,

818
01:06:54.990 --> 01:06:57.990
and that it will enable
all people to thrive.


819
01:06:58.350 --> 01:07:02.390
I don't forget my origins,
as memory is our best weapon.


820
01:07:02.550 --> 01:07:04.070
This is for you, Grandma!

821
01:07:04.230 --> 01:07:06.830
Free the protesters of Santa Adriana!

822
01:07:06.990 --> 01:07:09.470
From the turnstiles to the Convention!

823
01:07:09.670 --> 01:07:12.630
We students have made it here,
the humble will triumph.


824
01:07:12.790 --> 01:07:14.070
Thank you very much!

825
01:07:15.510 --> 01:07:18.070
I dared, because I needed to say:

826
01:07:18.230 --> 01:07:19.670
"The young people are here."

827
01:07:19.830 --> 01:07:21.070
Two years ago,

828
01:07:21.230 --> 01:07:23.550
we jumped over the subway turnstiles,

829
01:07:23.750 --> 01:07:26.110
now, I'm writing the new Constitution.

830
01:07:26.270 --> 01:07:29.230
So, it's really...

831
01:07:30.070 --> 01:07:32.310
As well as being gratifying,

832
01:07:34.310 --> 01:07:36.710
it is very moving to know,

833
01:07:37.710 --> 01:07:39.750
to be aware, now,

834
01:07:40.390 --> 01:07:43.470
that everything we went through
during the 2019 repression


835
01:07:43.670 --> 01:07:45.390
and everything that happened

836
01:07:45.550 --> 01:07:49.630
led to this amazing process
that we are experiencing today.


837
01:07:50.470 --> 01:07:54.670
We students made the first move,

838
01:07:55.190 --> 01:07:59.550
but it turned into a social struggle
of all Chilean people.


839
01:08:00.190 --> 01:08:02.350
What we are writing

840
01:08:02.510 --> 01:08:06.550
are the wishes of those who said:
"Enough!"


841
01:08:06.750 --> 01:08:10.710
We must build,
that is our main responsibility.


842
01:08:10.870 --> 01:08:13.550
Build and move forwards.

843
01:08:13.950 --> 01:08:16.670
And hopefully, in the future,

844
01:08:16.830 --> 01:08:20.110
we won't have to jump over
all those turnstiles,


845
01:08:20.270 --> 01:08:23.270
because I didn't just do it
on October 18,


846
01:08:23.430 --> 01:08:26.510
I had to jump over many more
to get this far.


847
01:08:42.030 --> 01:08:43.910
This is a solemn moment.

848
01:08:44.070 --> 01:08:47.390
I ask the members
of the Convention to rise,


849
01:08:47.550 --> 01:08:48.830
please.

850
01:08:52.070 --> 01:08:53.790
Now,

851
01:08:54.510 --> 01:08:59.710
in accordance with article 79
of the General Regulation,


852
01:09:00.350 --> 01:09:03.830
I declare, before the plenary Assembly,

853
01:09:03.990 --> 01:09:08.030
the official opening
of the constitutional debate.


854
01:09:08.190 --> 01:09:09.670
Elisa Loncón

855
01:09:09.990 --> 01:09:14.070
is the president
of the constituent Convention.


856
01:09:14.510 --> 01:09:17.110
She is also the first Mapuche woman

857
01:09:17.270 --> 01:09:20.630
to take on such a role
in the history of Chile.


858
01:09:23.830 --> 01:09:26.670
She makes us feel
this breath of fresh air


859
01:09:26.830 --> 01:09:28.870
that is traversing the country.

860
01:09:30.110 --> 01:09:33.070
Each day,
we deal with many things,


861
01:09:33.230 --> 01:09:37.790
but I am very happy
to be participating in this process.


862
01:09:39.430 --> 01:09:41.870
I am also happy for the Mapuche people,

863
01:09:42.030 --> 01:09:45.150
for the young people
and for all those women


864
01:09:45.310 --> 01:09:48.470
who see in me so many delays

865
01:09:48.670 --> 01:09:52.270
but, at the same time,
so many opportunities for action.


866
01:09:52.430 --> 01:09:57.190
That makes me so happy
and it fuels my dream of transformation.


867
01:09:57.990 --> 01:09:59.510
We are moving forward,

868
01:10:00.030 --> 01:10:02.470
we will achieve
the goal we set ourselves.


869
01:10:03.910 --> 01:10:05.870
When we Mapuche, say:

870
01:10:06.030 --> 01:10:06.950
<i>"marichiweu",</i>

871
01:10:07.110 --> 01:10:09.630
that means:
"We will never be overcome".


872
01:10:09.790 --> 01:10:14.350
It is a word that has historic importance

873
01:10:14.910 --> 01:10:17.110
and one that is also very colloquial.

874
01:10:17.270 --> 01:10:19.430
I learnt it from my grand-mother.

875
01:10:19.630 --> 01:10:22.790
Whenever she achieved something,
she said: "Marichiweu!"


876
01:10:22.950 --> 01:10:27.190
I understood that every achievement
should be accompanied by this word.


877
01:10:27.950 --> 01:10:31.110
Marichi means "forever",
and "marichiweu":


878
01:10:31.270 --> 01:10:32.790
"We will always win".

879
01:10:32.950 --> 01:10:35.270
You can also say "marichi poyeyu",

880
01:10:35.430 --> 01:10:38.030
"I will love you all my life".

881
01:10:38.190 --> 01:10:41.430
With "marichi",
you can create various combinations


882
01:10:41.630 --> 01:10:44.270
to express things that will last forever.

883
01:10:44.430 --> 01:10:46.630
It's a very pretty word.

884
01:10:55.310 --> 01:10:59.550
We also believed
in the permanent changes


885
01:10:59.750 --> 01:11:02.710
initiated by Salvador Allende.

886
01:11:05.270 --> 01:11:07.110
We were happy,

887
01:11:07.390 --> 01:11:11.390
but the coup d'État
shattered our lives and our dreams.


888
01:11:15.510 --> 01:11:18.750
Today, there is this new hope.

889
01:11:20.950 --> 01:11:23.670
I like to think
that the dream is finally happening


890
01:11:23.830 --> 01:11:28.230
and that the country we imagined
will become reality.


891
01:11:32.150 --> 01:11:37.350
This square has become the symbol
of the street fights,


892
01:11:37.750 --> 01:11:41.390
under the indifferent gaze
of General Baquedano,


893
01:11:41.790 --> 01:11:45.110
a military hero from the 19th century.

894
01:11:48.670 --> 01:11:52.950
Baquedano and his horse
would never have imagined


895
01:11:53.310 --> 01:11:58.030
that their statue would be the center
of these new struggles.


896
01:11:59.350 --> 01:12:01.870
The young people come here

897
01:12:02.030 --> 01:12:06.670
to transform this space
into a theater of the future.


898
01:12:14.550 --> 01:12:18.070
What is the greatest danger
that could happen?


899
01:12:18.470 --> 01:12:19.710
The first,

900
01:12:19.870 --> 01:12:22.430
would be if we lose faith
in the Convention


901
01:12:22.630 --> 01:12:26.990
to the point where the campaign
against the leaving referendum


902
01:12:27.150 --> 01:12:28.350
wins, for example,

903
01:12:28.510 --> 01:12:31.470
and we are left with
the dictator's Constitution.


904
01:12:31.670 --> 01:12:33.550
For me, that would be terrible.

905
01:12:33.750 --> 01:12:37.710
That could happen,
and it would be the worst thing.


906
01:12:38.230 --> 01:12:40.390
The second danger,

907
01:12:41.510 --> 01:12:43.630
is that many things

908
01:12:43.950 --> 01:12:48.910
have fueled a sense of patriotism

909
01:12:50.430 --> 01:12:52.270
that is very painful, in Chile.

910
01:12:52.750 --> 01:12:56.630
These two things together,
would be a terrible outcome.


911
01:12:56.790 --> 01:13:00.390
Firstly, that we fail
to drive a new Constitution,


912
01:13:00.710 --> 01:13:02.230
we would regret that.

913
01:13:02.390 --> 01:13:04.070
It would be a step backwards,

914
01:13:04.230 --> 01:13:08.390
regretting what we said
during the referendum,


915
01:13:08.550 --> 01:13:13.350
that we wanted a new Constitution
and that we should defend it.


916
01:13:13.750 --> 01:13:16.950
Secondly, that once again,

917
01:13:17.110 --> 01:13:19.990
far-right sectors of this country
are re-established,


918
01:13:20.150 --> 01:13:23.270
as has happened elsewhere
in Latin America and the world.


919
01:13:23.430 --> 01:13:26.070
That would be fatal.

920
01:13:27.870 --> 01:13:30.350
Is chess also a fight?

921
01:13:33.070 --> 01:13:36.430
It's a fight, a confrontation.

922
01:13:38.950 --> 01:13:41.270
It's also a space for meetings

923
01:13:41.430 --> 01:13:43.430
and discussions.

924
01:13:44.750 --> 01:13:48.630
According to the legend
of the Goddess of chess, Caïssa,


925
01:13:49.150 --> 01:13:52.310
who, at some point, was linked to war,

926
01:13:52.470 --> 01:13:57.110
she said:
"Listen, make war on a chessboard.


927
01:13:57.270 --> 01:14:00.110
"Converse, think, imagine, create

928
01:14:00.270 --> 01:14:02.630
"and stop making war outside".

929
01:14:02.790 --> 01:14:06.230
But there is a fight.

930
01:14:06.390 --> 01:14:07.830
Someone dies.

931
01:14:08.350 --> 01:14:09.750
Yes, of course.

932
01:14:10.150 --> 01:14:11.830
You must destroy...

933
01:14:12.670 --> 01:14:14.310
You must capture, rather.

934
01:14:14.470 --> 01:14:16.910
You capture, you never kill.

935
01:14:17.070 --> 01:14:18.070
We capture.

936
01:14:18.230 --> 01:14:19.750
There is a fair trial.

937
01:14:19.910 --> 01:14:22.550
The King is allowed a fair trial.

938
01:14:45.150 --> 01:14:49.550
In order to preserve it,
the military removed the statue.


939
01:14:49.910 --> 01:14:53.390
Even so, they built a high fence

940
01:14:53.550 --> 01:14:55.550
around the empty stand.

941
01:14:56.070 --> 01:14:58.270
That provoked indignation.

942
01:14:59.310 --> 01:15:03.990
A huge crowd converged in the square
on the second anniversary


943
01:15:04.150 --> 01:15:05.270
of the outburst.

944
01:16:43.870 --> 01:16:48.990
Everything indicates
that we have reached the end of an era.


945
01:16:49.430 --> 01:16:52.630
I feel a new era is beginning.

946
01:16:54.750 --> 01:16:56.990
At the same time,

947
01:16:57.390 --> 01:17:01.110
Chile is voting
for a new president of the Republic.


948
01:17:02.230 --> 01:17:05.670
The candidate Gabriel Boric wins.

949
01:17:06.990 --> 01:17:10.830
He wins it by 4,600,000 votes

950
01:17:11.270 --> 01:17:14.270
against the far-right candidate.

951
01:17:17.350 --> 01:17:19.750
He triumphs thanks to the huge support

952
01:17:19.910 --> 01:17:22.670
of young people, women,

953
01:17:22.830 --> 01:17:26.070
and of all Chileans who wish for change.

954
01:17:39.310 --> 01:17:41.950
These stones now form

955
01:17:42.310 --> 01:17:44.710
the foundations of a new house,

956
01:17:44.870 --> 01:17:49.070
in which Chile will open its windows wide

957
01:17:49.470 --> 01:17:51.830
to let the air circulate.

958
01:17:56.310 --> 01:17:59.790
I am beginning to see
a new imaginary country.


959
01:18:16.950 --> 01:18:18.510
Good evening, Chile!

960
01:18:21.230 --> 01:18:22.310
<i>Po nui</i>

961
01:18:22.950 --> 01:18:26.470
<i>suma aruma, pun may, Chile!</i>

962
01:18:28.870 --> 01:18:30.390
Thank you all,

963
01:18:30.990 --> 01:18:32.990
every one of you,

964
01:18:33.150 --> 01:18:36.990
all peoples who live
in this place we call Chile.


965
01:18:39.910 --> 01:18:43.350
Today, hope overcame fear!

966
01:18:47.510 --> 01:18:51.710
As you know, I come from far away,

967
01:18:51.870 --> 01:18:55.830
from the South, from Magallanes,
on the edge of the Antarctic,


968
01:18:55.990 --> 01:18:57.670
and I am 35 years old.

969
01:19:00.110 --> 01:19:04.630
I am fully aware
that history doesn't start with us.


970
01:19:04.790 --> 01:19:07.230
I feel like an heir,

971
01:19:07.750 --> 01:19:10.510
and that our project is the heir

972
01:19:10.710 --> 01:19:13.190
of a long historical trajectory,

973
01:19:13.350 --> 01:19:16.230
that of those whom,
from various positions,


974
01:19:16.390 --> 01:19:20.190
have searched tirelessly for justice,

975
01:19:20.510 --> 01:19:22.550
the expansion of democracy,

976
01:19:22.750 --> 01:19:25.030
the defense of human rights,

977
01:19:25.190 --> 01:19:27.030
and the protection of freedoms.

978
01:19:27.190 --> 01:19:30.830
That, my large family,
is what I want to see reunited


979
01:19:30.990 --> 01:19:33.310
in this chapter which we are initiating.

980
01:19:33.470 --> 01:19:35.990
We are facing an historic change of cycle

981
01:19:36.150 --> 01:19:37.830
that we cannot lose out on!

982
01:19:39.550 --> 01:19:42.790
I would like to thank, in particular,

983
01:19:42.950 --> 01:19:45.310
the women of our homeland.

984
01:19:48.150 --> 01:19:51.670
They came together,
throughout the entire country,


985
01:19:51.830 --> 01:19:56.150
to defend the rights
that they had such difficulty obtaining.


986
01:19:58.110 --> 01:20:01.550
From things so basic
as the right to vote,


987
01:20:01.750 --> 01:20:05.910
to the right to be in charge
of their own bodies.


988
01:20:07.510 --> 01:20:10.670
From the right to non-discrimination...